🔐 SQL Injection Detection & Analysis using Splunk
Recently, I worked on detecting SQL Injection (SQLi) attacks by analyzing web server logs in Splunk. The dashboard identifies suspicious SQL keywords such as SELECT, UNION, DROP, INSERT, OR 1=1, SLEEP(), and other malicious patterns commonly used by attackers.
✅ Monitored HTTP requests and URI queries
✅ Detected encoded and non-encoded SQL injection attempts
✅ Classified events based on severity (Medium, High, Critical)
✅ Visualized attack trends and suspicious activities through dashboards
✅ Improved visibility into potential web application threats
This exercise helped me gain hands-on experience in log analysis, threat detection, Splunk SPL queries, and web application security monitoring.
